record_data.record_plain_text: Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service PSEG Energy Resources & Trade LLC (???PSEG ER&T???) provides Reactive Supply and Voltage from Generation Sources Service (???Reactive Supply Service???) from various generating facilities to the PJM Interconnection, LLC (???PJM???) system. This Rate Schedule, which consists of seventeen separate tariff sections for each of PSEG ER&T???s generating facilities, sets forth PSEG ER&T???s revenue requirements for the provision of Reactive Supply Service to PJM, as contemplated by Schedule 2 of the PJM open access transmission tariff. PSEG ER&T???s total monthly revenue requirement consists of the sum of the charges for the following: (1) the Fixed Capability Revenue Requirement; and (2) the Heating Losses Component for each of its generating facilities. The Fixed Capability Revenue Requirement: the Heating Losses Component, and the Total Revenue Requirements for each generating facility is set forth in the Rate Schedule below. This Rate Schedule and its separate sections shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission. Nothing contained herein shall be construed as affecting in any way the right of PSEG ER&T to unilaterally make application to the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission for a change in rates under section 205 of the Federal Power Act and pursuant to the Commission's Rules and Regulations promulgated thereunder. If PSEG ER&T seeks to change one of the revenue requirements stated herein, it will abide by relevant FERC procedures for changes in rates and notify PJM in accordance with any notice requirement in the PJM Tariff.
